### HYMN CVI

#### A charm to protect a house from fire

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0610601">1</span></span>Let flowery
Dūrvā grass grow up about thine exit and  
   approach.  
  There let a spring of water rise, or lake with blooming lotuses.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0610602">2</span></span>This is the
place where waters meet, here is the gathering of the  
   flood.  
  Our home is set amid the lake: turn thou thy jaws away from  
   it.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0610603">3</span></span>O House, we
compass thee about with coolness to envelop thee.  
  Cool as a lake be thou to us. Let Agni bring us healing balm!

